I LOVED THE ATTENTION SO MUCH
THAT I DIDN'T REALIZE

205
00:09:38,822 --> 00:09:41,222
WHAT MY SON REALLY NEEDED
THE MOST --

206
00:09:41,322 --> 00:09:44,189
THE CHANCE TO BE A NORMAL KID
ONCE IN A WHILE.

207
00:09:44,289 --> 00:09:47,189
I HATE TO SAY IT,
BUT WE FAILED AS PARENTS.

208
00:09:47,289 --> 00:09:48,655
YOU'RE RIGHT.

209
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:51,322
KEN, PLEASE WAKE UP.

210
00:09:51,422 --> 00:09:53,322
KEN, PLEASE GIVE US
ANOTHER CHANCE

211
00:09:53,422 --> 00:09:55,322
TO BE BETTER PARENTS
TO YOU.

212
00:09:55,422 --> 00:09:57,322
[ Thinking ]
<i>I CAN'T WAKE UP YET.</i>

213
00:09:57,422 --> 00:09:59,322
<i>I STILL HAVEN'T FOUND</i>
<i>MY HEART.</i>

214
00:09:59,422 --> 00:10:02,322
<i>I'M STILL TRYING TO GET BACK</i>
<i>TO THAT LITTLE KID</i>

215
00:10:02,422 --> 00:10:05,255
<i>THAT USED TO BLOW BUBBLES</i>
<i>ON HIS TERRACE.</i>

216
00:10:05,355 --> 00:10:07,255
<i>I'D STAND THERE FOR HOURS,</i>

217
00:10:07,355 --> 00:10:09,729
<i>BLOWING THEM</i>
<i>BIGGER AND BIGGER EACH TIME.</i>

218
00:10:09,829 --> 00:10:11,729
<i>EACH ONE</i>
<i>WAS COMPLETELY EMPTY INSIDE,</i>

219
00:10:11,829 --> 00:10:14,729
<i>BUT NONE OF THEM WERE</i>
<i>AS EMPTY INSIDE AS I WAS.</i>

220
00:10:14,829 --> 00:10:17,729
<i>MAYBE I WAS TRYING TO SHOW SAM</i>
<i>THAT I COULD BLOW BUBBLES</i>

221
00:10:17,829 --> 00:10:19,262
<i>BIGGER THAN HE COULD,</i>

222
00:10:19,362 --> 00:10:22,229
<i>AND THAT I WAS BETTER</i>
<i>AT SOMETHING THAN HE WAS.</i>

223
00:10:22,329 --> 00:10:23,895
<i>BUT THEN AGAIN,</i>

224
00:10:23,995 --> 00:10:26,895
<i>WHO WAS IT THAT TAUGHT ME</i>
<i>TO BLOW THE BUBBLES?</i>

225
00:10:26,995 --> 00:10:31,162
<i>IT WASN'T MY PARENTS.</i>
<i>IT WAS SAM.</i>

226
00:10:31,262 --> 00:10:33,162
KEN, IT'S ALL SET TO GO.

227
00:10:33,262 --> 00:10:35,362
THANKS, SAM.

228
00:10:35,462 --> 00:10:38,829
THATABOY.
WOW, GREAT!

229
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:40,395
HA HA HA!

230
00:10:40,495 --> 00:10:42,729
HA HA! YOU TRY
TO DO IT NOW.

231
00:10:42,829 --> 00:10:45,729
OH, WELL, I'M NOT VERY GOOD
AT BLOWING BUBBLES.

232
00:10:45,829 --> 00:10:47,229
COME ON, SAM,

233
00:10:47,329 --> 00:10:49,662
THERE'S NOTHING IN THIS WORLD
THAT YOU CAN'T DO.

234
00:10:49,762 --> 00:10:51,162
I CAN DO IT OKAY,

235
00:10:51,262 --> 00:10:54,162
BUT MY TECHNIQUE ISN'T
QUITE AS GOOD AS YOURS IS.

236
00:10:54,262 --> 00:10:56,795
YOUR BUBBLES COME OUT PERFECT
BECAUSE YOU'RE GENTLE.

237
00:10:56,895 --> 00:10:59,495
I BLOW TOO HARD,
AND MINE POP RIGHT AWAY.

238
00:10:59,595 --> 00:11:02,329
HUH? WHERE'D YOU GO?

239
00:11:02,429 --> 00:11:05,329
SAM, COME BACK.
PLEASE!

240
00:11:05,429 --> 00:11:08,169
<i>BUT SAM WON'T COME BACK.</i>
<i>HE'S GONE FOREVER.</i>

241
00:11:08,269 --> 00:11:09,935
<i>MAYBE I AM, TOO.</i>

242
00:11:11,969 --> 00:11:13,502
HE'S AWAKE!

243
00:11:13,602 --> 00:11:15,402
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

244
00:11:15,502 --> 00:11:18,802
WHO ARE YOU? WELL?

245
00:11:18,902 --> 00:11:21,269
KEN, DON'T YOU RECOGNIZE
WHO WE ARE?

246
00:11:21,369 --> 00:11:23,269
IT'S AMNESIA!

247
00:11:23,369 --> 00:11:26,269
[ Thinking ] <i>NO, I DIDN'T LOSE</i>
<i>MY MEMORY, I LOST MY HEART.</i>

248
00:11:26,369 --> 00:11:29,269
<i>AND UNTIL I FIND IT,</i>
<i>I DON'T KNOW WHO I AM,</i>

249
00:11:29,369 --> 00:11:31,569
<i>OR WHO ANYONE ELSE IS,</i>
<i>EITHER.</i>

250
00:11:31,669 --> 00:11:35,035
HOW COULD HE NOT KNOW
WHO HIS OWN PARENTS ARE?

251
00:11:35,135 --> 00:11:37,035
<i>YOU DON'T KNOW ME, EITHER.</i>

252
00:11:37,135 --> 00:11:40,002
<i>HOW COULD YOU,</i>
<i>IF I DON'T KNOW MYSELF?</i>

253
00:11:40,102 --> 00:11:42,235
<i>WHO AM I?</i>

254
00:11:42,335 --> 00:11:44,669
KEN, DON'T WORRY.
YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

255
00:11:44,769 --> 00:11:47,169
WE'LL FIND YOU THE FINEST
DOCTOR IN THE WORLD.

256
00:11:47,269 --> 00:11:48,669
WHILE YOU WERE
SLEEPING,

257
00:11:48,769 --> 00:11:51,602
YOUR MOTHER AND I REALIZED
WE TRIED TO MAKE YOU

258
00:11:51,702 --> 00:11:53,935
MORE LIKE SAM
WITHOUT REALLY KNOWING IT.

259
00:11:54,035 --> 00:11:56,435
WE'RE SORRY. WE SHOULD'VE
SEEN THE SON WE HAD,

260
00:11:56,535 --> 00:11:58,435
INSTEAD OF SPENDING TIME
CONSTANTLY LOOKING

261
00:11:58,535 --> 00:12:00,435
FOR THE SON WE LOST.

262
00:12:00,535 --> 00:12:01,502
FORGIVE US.

263
00:12:01,602 --> 00:12:03,902
ALL WE'RE ASKING
FOR IS A SECOND CHANCE.

264
00:12:04,002 --> 00:12:06,402
<i>I DON'T KNOW</i>
<i>WHAT THEY WANT FROM ME.</i>

265
00:12:06,502 --> 00:12:09,209
<i>HOW CAN I FORGIVE THEM</i>
<i>WHEN I DON'T UNDERSTAND</i>

266
00:12:09,309 --> 00:12:10,675
<i>WHAT THEY DID?</i>

267
00:12:10,775 --> 00:12:14,309
SAM IS GONE FOREVER, BUT WE
DON'T WANT TO LOSE YOU, TOO.

268
00:12:14,409 --> 00:12:16,942
JUST BE KEN.
JUST BE YOUR SWEET SELF.

269
00:12:17,042 --> 00:12:21,275
KEN, JUST TRY.
JUST TRY, PLEASE, FOR ME.

270
00:12:21,375 --> 00:12:24,109
<i>WHY IS SHE CRYING?</i>
<i>I DON'T UNDERSTAND.</i>

271
00:12:24,209 --> 00:12:26,775
<i>WHEN I'M SAD,</i>
<i>I JUST GO NUMB.</i>

272
00:12:26,875 --> 00:12:29,609
<i>WAIT. THERE'S TEARS</i>
<i>IN MY EYES, TOO.</i>

273
00:12:29,709 --> 00:12:31,442
<i>WHY AM I CRYING?</i>

274
00:12:31,542 --> 00:12:34,242
<i>IS MY HEART CLOSER</i>
<i>THAN I THINK?</i>

275
00:12:34,342 --> 00:12:37,775
<i>MAYBE THESE PEOPLE AND I</i>
<i>CAN SHARE THE PAIN AND SORROW</i>

276
00:12:37,875 --> 00:12:39,709
<i>OF LOSING SAM TOGETHER.</i>

277
00:12:39,809 --> 00:12:42,109
<i>I'M STILL SEARCHING.</i>

278
00:12:42,209 --> 00:12:44,609
<i>I KNOW THE ANSWER</i>
<i>IS OUT THERE.</i>

279
00:12:44,709 --> 00:12:47,175
<i>I JUST HAVE TO FIGURE OUT</i>
<i>WHERE TO LOOK.</i>

280
00:12:47,275 --> 00:12:48,875
KEN, HONEY,
DINNER'S READY.

281
00:12:48,975 --> 00:12:50,042
HUNGRY?

282
00:12:50,142 --> 00:12:51,142
[ GASPS ]

283
00:12:51,242 --> 00:12:53,609
OH, SORRY
I STARTLED YOU.

284
00:12:53,709 --> 00:12:57,275
UH...IT'S OKAY. YOU CAN EAT
WHENEVER YOU'RE READY.

285
00:13:00,542 --> 00:13:02,475
THAT'S SAM.
HE WAS YOUR BROTHER.

286
00:13:02,575 --> 00:13:05,042
WE WERE ALL DEVASTATED
AFTER SAM'S ACCIDENT,

287
00:13:05,142 --> 00:13:09,415
BUT YOU WERE THE ONE
AFFECTED THE MOST.

288
00:13:12,915 --> 00:13:15,882
<i>I KNOW WHAT THAT IS.</i>

289
00:13:18,849 --> 00:13:21,649
PLEASE, MASTER,
LISTEN TO ME.

290
00:13:21,749 --> 00:13:23,749
WHERE'S THE KEN
I USED TO LOVE?

291
00:13:23,849 --> 00:13:25,715
OH, WORMMON.

292
00:13:25,815 --> 00:13:27,682
I KNOW WHERE
TO LOOK NOW.

293
00:13:27,782 --> 00:13:31,382
KEN, DEAR. I MADE YOU
A NICE CUP OF TEA.

294
00:13:31,482 --> 00:13:33,315
KEN, WHERE ARE YOU?

295
00:13:33,415 --> 00:13:35,282
NOT AGAIN.

296
00:13:35,382 --> 00:13:37,749
<i>I KNOW THIS PLACE.</i>

297
00:13:37,849 --> 00:13:40,215
<i>I'VE BEEN HERE BEFORE.</i>

298
00:13:40,315 --> 00:13:42,715
<i>THIS IS WHERE</i>
<i>I HAVE TO LOOK.</i>

299
00:13:42,815 --> 00:13:47,715
<i>I KNOW THAT THIS IS WHERE</i>
<i>I WILL FIND MY HEART.</i>

300
00:13:47,815 --> 00:13:51,149
<i>DIGIEGGS --</i>
<i>HUNDREDS OF THEM!</i>

301
00:13:51,249 --> 00:13:53,482
<i>WHAT IS THIS PLACE?</i>

302
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:00,620
THIS IS
THE PRIMARY VILLAGE.
PRIMARY VILLAGE?

303
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:02,253
THAT'S RIGHT.

304
00:14:02,353 --> 00:14:04,753
THIS IS THE PLACE
WHERE ALL DIGIMON ARE REBORN,

305
00:14:04,853 --> 00:14:07,220
AND THEY COME BACK
AS DIGIEGGS.

306
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:08,527
WORMMON, TOO?

307
00:14:08,627 --> 00:14:11,493
DIGIMON NEVER DIE.
THEY JUST GET RECONFIGURED.

308
00:14:11,593 --> 00:14:13,160
HA HA HA!

309
00:14:16,193 --> 00:14:19,460
WHICH EGG IS WORMMON'S?
IT COULD BE ANY ONE OF THEM.

310
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:22,627
I CAN'T REMEMBER.
WHAT DID HIS EGG LOOK LIKE?

311
00:14:22,727 --> 00:14:25,627
I DON'T KNOW WHICH ONE
OF THESE DIGIEGGS IS WORMMON'S,

312
00:14:25,727 --> 00:14:28,627
JUST LIKE I DON'T REMEMBER
WHO I AM OR WHERE I'M FROM.

313
00:14:28,727 --> 00:14:31,427
Voice: YOU'RE THE DIGIMON
EMPEROR, AREN'T YOU?

314
00:14:31,527 --> 00:14:34,860
I RECOGNIZE YOU EVEN WITHOUT
YOUR FANCY CLOTHES.

315
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,193
HYAH!

316
00:14:36,293 --> 00:14:37,793
HUH? THE DIGIMON
EMPEROR?

317
00:14:37,893 --> 00:14:40,293
THAT'S RIGHT. I WAS
THE DIGIMON EMPEROR.

318
00:14:40,393 --> 00:14:42,227
I'VE DONE SO MANY
TERRIBLE THINGS.

319
00:14:42,327 --> 00:14:44,227
IF I WOULD'VE REALIZED
THE TRUTH

320
00:14:44,327 --> 00:14:46,727
ABOUT THE DIGIWORLD
SOONER,

321
00:14:46,827 --> 00:14:49,427
WORMMON WOULD STILL BE HERE
WITH ME TODAY.

322
00:14:49,527 --> 00:14:51,927
YOU DON'T WANT TO FIND
WORMMON'S DIGIEGG

323
00:14:52,027 --> 00:14:54,427
BECAUSE YOU MISS HIM,

324
00:14:54,527 --> 00:14:56,927
YOU JUST DON'T WANT
TO FEEL GUILTY ANYMORE

325
00:14:57,027 --> 00:14:58,893
OVER CAUSING
HIS DESTRUCTION.

326
00:14:58,993 --> 00:15:01,393
WHAT DO YOU THINK'S
GOING TO HAPPEN,

327
00:15:01,493 --> 00:15:03,393
WORMMON'S JUST GOING
TO HATCH

328
00:15:03,493 --> 00:15:05,893
SO HE CAN BE TREATED BADLY
BY YOU AGAIN?

329
00:15:05,993 --> 00:15:07,960
WORMMON WON'T COME BACK
TO ME?

330
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:10,700
JUST LIKE MY BROTHER SAM
DIDN'T COME BACK TO ME

331
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,233
AFTER HE LEFT.

332
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:14,233
[ Thinking ]
<i>WORMMON'S NOT COMING BACK.</i>

333
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:16,233
<i>SAM'S NOT COMING BACK,</i>
<i>EITHER.</i>

334
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:18,733
<i>I CAUSED BOTH OF THEM</i>
<i>TO GO AWAY.</i>

335
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:21,733
<i>I HATED MY BROTHER FOR GETTING</i>
<i>ALL OF THE ATTENTION.</i>

336
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:24,733
<i>I HATED WORMMON BECAUSE I FELT</i>
<i>HE WASN'T WORTHY OF ME.</i>

337
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:27,333
THE TRUTH IS,
I WASN'T WORTHY OF HIM.

338
00:15:27,433 --> 00:15:30,400
<i>THESE HANDS -- THESE HANDS</i>
<i>HAVE CAUSED SO MUCH PAIN.</i>

339
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:33,567
<i>SURE, PUT A TEXTBOOK IN THEM,</i>
<i>AND I'M A GENIUS,</i>

340
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:35,567
<i>BUT PUT A WHIP IN THEM,</i>

341
00:15:35,667 --> 00:15:37,567
<i>AND I'M THE EVIL</i>
<i>DIGIMON EMPEROR.</i>

342
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:40,567
<i>HOW COULD I HAVE ALLOWED THIS</i>
<i>TO GO SO FAR?</i>

343
00:15:40,667 --> 00:15:44,167
IF I ONLY HAD THE CHANCE,
I'D SAY, SORRY, SAM.

344
00:15:44,267 --> 00:15:47,767
I'M SORRY, WORMMON!

345
00:15:47,867 --> 00:15:51,567
GOODBYE, KEN.

346
00:15:53,867 --> 00:15:56,067
WORMMON, NO.

347
00:15:58,100 --> 00:16:00,567
IT'S TOO LATE NOW.
WHAT'S DONE IS DONE.

348
00:16:00,667 --> 00:16:03,067
YOU'VE MADE YOUR BED,
NOW LIE IN IT.

349
00:16:03,167 --> 00:16:06,267
I'D GO ON, BUT I CAN'T THINK
OF ANY MORE CLICHéS.

350
00:16:06,367 --> 00:16:08,773
YOU CAN'T RUN AWAY
FROM THE PAST.

351
00:16:08,873 --> 00:16:11,240
WHY DON'T YOU CRAWL BACK
UNDER THE CONTROL SPIRE

352
00:16:11,340 --> 00:16:13,240
YOU CAME OUT OF?

353
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:14,740
CAN'T I START OVER?

354
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,740
I KNOW I'VE CAUSED YOU ALL
A LOT OF PAIN

355
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:20,240
AS THE DIGIMON EMPEROR,
BUT I'M TRULY SORRY NOW.

356
00:16:20,340 --> 00:16:22,207
THE CRUEL THINGS I'VE DONE

357
00:16:22,307 --> 00:16:24,707
IN THE PAST
WON'T EVER LEAVE ME,

358
00:16:24,807 --> 00:16:27,207
BUT I'VE GOT TO MOVE ON
WITH MY LIFE.

359
00:16:27,307 --> 00:16:30,173
I PROMISE TO CONCENTRATE
ON THE GOOD THINGS IN THE PAST.

360
00:16:30,273 --> 00:16:32,673
I'LL USE MY MEMORIES OF SAM
AND OF WORMMON

361
00:16:32,773 --> 00:16:34,140
TO MAKE ME STRONGER,

362
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:37,140
BUT I CAN'T SEEM TO REMEMBER
ANY OF THE GOOD MEMORIES.

363
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:41,173
ONLY THE BAD ONES KEEP PLAYING
IN MY HEAD OVER AND OVER AGAIN.

364
00:16:41,273 --> 00:16:43,607
I MUST FORCE MYSELF
TO REMEMBER THE BEGINNING.

365
00:16:43,707 --> 00:16:45,107
I MUST THINK BACK

366
00:16:45,207 --> 00:16:47,607
TO THE FIRST TIME
I USED SAM'S DIGEVICE

367
00:16:47,707 --> 00:16:49,640
TO GO TO THE DIGITAL WORLD.

368
00:16:52,107 --> 00:16:53,507
HYAH!

369
00:16:53,607 --> 00:16:54,473
AAH!

370
00:16:54,573 --> 00:16:57,440
WORMMON!

371
00:16:57,540 --> 00:16:59,107
WORMMON, YOU OKAY?

372
00:16:59,207 --> 00:17:00,607
I'M OKAY.

373
00:17:00,707 --> 00:17:03,607
IT WILL TAKE A LOT MORE
THAN HIM TO BEAT ME.

374
00:17:03,707 --> 00:17:06,340
KEN, I'M REALLY GLAD
THAT I'M YOUR DIGIMON

375
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:08,347
AND WE'RE PARTNERS.

376
00:17:08,447 --> 00:17:11,047
YOU'RE GENTLE AND KIND.
THAT'S WHY I LIKE YOU.

377
00:17:11,147 --> 00:17:13,013
I'M GENTLE?

378
00:17:13,113 --> 00:17:15,513
YOUR BUBBLES COME OUT PERFECT
BECAUSE YOU'RE GENTLE.

379
00:17:15,613 --> 00:17:18,713
I BLOW TOO HARD,
AND MINE POP RIGHT AWAY.

380
00:17:18,813 --> 00:17:21,180
BUT BEING GENTLE
IS NOT ENOUGH.

381
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:23,680
YOU HAVE TO BE STRONG,
AS WELL.

382
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:24,880
OTHERWISE, KEN --

383
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:26,047
OTHERWISE, WHAT?

384
00:17:26,147 --> 00:17:27,547
YOUR GENTLENESS
AND KINDNESS

385
00:17:27,647 --> 00:17:30,047
WILL BECOME OVERPOWERED
BY THOSE WHO ARE EVIL.

386
00:17:30,147 --> 00:17:31,147
IT HAPPENS.

387
00:17:31,247 --> 00:17:33,147
THE DIGEVICE
THAT YOU HAVE

388
00:17:33,247 --> 00:17:35,147
BELONGS TO YOU
AND NOT SAM.

389
00:17:35,247 --> 00:17:38,613
YOU'RE DIGIDESTINED, AND NO ONE
CAN TAKE THAT AWAY FROM YOU.

390
00:17:38,713 --> 00:17:41,113
EVIL FORCES WILL TRY
TO TELL YOU OTHERWISE.

391
00:17:41,213 --> 00:17:43,047
NEVER FORGET WHO YOU ARE.

392
00:17:43,147 --> 00:17:44,313
I WON'T.

393
00:17:44,413 --> 00:17:46,713
YOU PROMISE?

394
00:17:46,813 --> 00:17:49,713
I BROKE MY PROMISE
BECAUSE I DID FORGET.

395
00:17:49,813 --> 00:17:52,713
MY WHOLE LIFE, I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO BE SOMEONE ELSE,

396
00:17:52,813 --> 00:17:55,713
WHETHER IT WAS ACTING TOUGH
AS THE DIGIMON EMPEROR

397
00:17:55,813 --> 00:17:58,380
OR TRYING TO BE
MORE LIKE SAM.

398
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,047
I'VE NEVER BEEN KEN,

399
00:18:00,147 --> 00:18:02,547
BUT I'M GOING TO SPEND
THE REST OF MY LIFE

400
00:18:02,647 --> 00:18:06,380
BEING THE KIND OF GENTLE PERSON
THAT WORMMON WANTED ME TO BE.

401
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:09,253
HUH?

402
00:18:09,353 --> 00:18:10,253
WHAT'S THIS?

403
00:18:10,353 --> 00:18:12,220
THAT'S YOUR CREST
OF KINDNESS.

404
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:14,920
ARE YOU SURE IT'S MINE?

405
00:18:15,020 --> 00:18:18,620
KEN, PLEASE FIND ME.
PLEASE FIND ME SOON.

406
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:21,087
THAT DIGIEGG IS DIFFERENT
FROM THE OTHERS.

407
00:18:21,187 --> 00:18:22,553
HURRY, KEN.

408
00:18:22,653 --> 00:18:25,520
SOMETHING TELLS ME
I'VE SEEN IT BEFORE.

409
00:18:25,620 --> 00:18:28,553
IT'S GLOWING, JUST LIKE
THE CREST OF KINDNESS.

410
00:18:32,853 --> 00:18:35,820
WHO ARE YOU?

411
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:37,987
HI, KEN.

412
00:18:39,753 --> 00:18:43,053
I'M LEAFMON,
THE BABY FORM OF WORMMON.

413
00:18:43,153 --> 00:18:45,653
I KEPT SEARCHING FOR YOU.
I NEVER STOPPED.

414
00:18:45,753 --> 00:18:47,153
KEN, THANK YOU.

415
00:18:47,253 --> 00:18:49,653
YOU TOOK A LITTLE DETOUR
IN GETTING THERE,

416
00:18:49,753 --> 00:18:51,653
BUT YOU KEPT
YOUR PROMISE.

417
00:18:51,753 --> 00:18:53,520
WHAT PROMISE?

418
00:18:53,620 --> 00:18:55,020
BEING KIND AND GENTLE.

419
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:58,020
THANK YOU FOR GIVING ME
A SECOND CHANCE.

420
00:19:01,853 --> 00:19:03,320
Ken: [ Thinking ]
<i>I WONDER,</i>

421
00:19:03,420 --> 00:19:06,320
<i>IF WAS THE ONE WHO WAS GONE</i>
<i>INSTEAD OF SAM,</i>

422
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:09,327
<i>WOULD WORMMON BE THE ONLY ONE</i>
<i>WHO WOULD MISS ME?</i>

423
00:19:09,427 --> 00:19:11,427
<i>HMM. NO, I DON'T THINK SO.</i>

424
00:19:11,527 --> 00:19:13,927
THIS TIME HE MIGHT NOT
COME BACK AT ALL.

425
00:19:14,027 --> 00:19:15,427
DON'T SAY SUCH THINGS.

426
00:19:15,527 --> 00:19:17,993
HE'LL BE BACK,
I'M SURE OF IT.

427
00:19:18,093 --> 00:19:19,327
KEN!
KEN!

428
00:19:19,427 --> 00:19:20,893
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

429
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:24,027
WE'VE BEEN SO WORRIED
ABOUT YOU.

430
00:19:24,127 --> 00:19:26,527
[ Thinking ] <i>NOW I UNDERSTAND</i>
<i>WHY SHE'S CRYING.</i>

431
00:19:26,627 --> 00:19:29,527
<i>SHE MISSED ME, JUST LIKE</i>
<i>I MISSED WORMMON.</i>

432
00:19:29,627 --> 00:19:30,993
MAMA.

433
00:19:31,093 --> 00:19:32,993
HUH? WHAT DID YOU SAY?

434
00:19:33,093 --> 00:19:36,960
HE SAID "MAMA."
THAT MEANS HE KNOWS ME.

435
00:19:37,060 --> 00:19:39,493
MAMA, I'LL GIVE YOU
THAT SECOND CHANCE

436
00:19:39,593 --> 00:19:42,093
IF I CAN HAVE ONE.

437
00:19:42,193 --> 00:19:45,060
[ CRYING ]

438
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:48,660
THANKS FOR BEING
SUCH GREAT PARENTS.

439
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:51,527
[ ALL CRYING ]

440
00:19:51,627 --> 00:19:54,527
Ken: [ Thinking ] <i>AND NOW</i>
<i>I CAN FINALLY SAY IT --</i>

441
00:19:54,627 --> 00:19:57,960
<i>THANK YOU, SAM,</i>
<i>FOR HELPING ME FIND MY HEART.</i>

442
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,893
[ SIGHS ]

443
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:05,893
Man: <i>NOW THAT KEN IS NO LONGER</i>
<i>THE DIGIMON EMPEROR,</i>

444
00:20:05,993 --> 00:20:07,893
<i>WILL HE JOIN THE DIGIDESTINED?</i>

445
00:20:07,993 --> 00:20:11,100
<i>FIND OUT ON THE NEXT</i>
<i>"DIGIMON -- DIGITAL MONSTERS."</i>

